Enum Constant Detail

NOERROR

public static final ErrorInfo NOERROR
No error has occurred.
The function executed successfully.

BADCOUNTER

public static final ErrorInfo BADCOUNTER
Invalid counter specified.
The specified counter number does not exist on the device.

BADADCHAN

public static final ErrorInfo BADADCHAN
Invalid A/D channel number.
An invalid channel argument was passed to an analog input function. The range of valid channel numbers is device-dependent.

BADCOUNT

public static final ErrorInfo BADCOUNT
Invalid count.
An invalid count argument was specified. If this error occurs during an analog input scanning operation increase the count value.

BADDAVAL

public static final ErrorInfo BADDAVAL
Invalid D/A value.
An invalid D/A value was passed to an analog output function. Legal values are 0 to 4,095 for 12-bit devices and 0 to 65,535 for 16-bit devices.

BADDACHAN

public static final ErrorInfo BADDACHAN
Invalid D/A channel number.
An invalid channel argument was passed to an analog output function. The range of valid channel numbers is device-dependent.

ALREADYACTIVE

public static final ErrorInfo ALREADYACTIVE
Background operation already in progress.
An attempt was made to start a second background process before the first process has completed. To stop a background operation, call the stopBackground() method for the specific function type. To wait for a background process to complete, call getStatus() and wait for currentStatus=Status.IDLE.

BADRATE

public static final ErrorInfo BADRATE
Invalid sampling rate.
Invalid sampling rate argument was specified. The rate was either zero, a negative number, or a rate faster than supported by the device.

OVERRUN

public static final ErrorInfo OVERRUN
Data overrun – data was lost.
Data was lost during an analog input operation because the computer could not keep up with the A/D sampling rate. This typically can only happen with the file input functions or by using SINGLIO mode. Possible solutions include lowering the sampling rate or lowering the count.

BADRANGE

public static final ErrorInfo BADRANGE
Invalid voltage or current range.
Invalid range argument was specified to an analog input or output function. Valid ranges are device-dependent.

BADDEVICETYPE

public static final ErrorInfo BADDEVICETYPE
This function cannot be used with this device.
An attempt was made to call a function for a device for which it is not supported.

PORTNOTCONFIGURABLE

public static final ErrorInfo PORTNOTCONFIGURABLE
Digital port is not configurable.

BADTRIGTYPE

public static final ErrorInfo BADTRIGTYPE
Invalid trigger type. The setTrigger() method was called with an invalid TriggerType argument. It must be set to either TRIG_ABOVE or TRIG_BELOW.

BADOPTION

public static final ErrorInfo BADOPTION
Invalid option specified for this function.
The specified option is not valid for the function.

BADBITNUMBER

public static final ErrorInfo BADBITNUMBER
Invalid bit number.
An invalid bitNum value was passed to a digital function. The valid range of bit numbers is device-dependent.

UNDERRUN

public static final ErrorInfo UNDERRUN
D/A FIFO went empty during output.
The specified D/A output rate could not be sustained. Try increasing the size of the data buffer or reducing the update rate to eliminate the error.

OPENCONNECTION

public static final ErrorInfo OPENCONNECTION
Temperature input has open connection

BADEVENTTYPE

public static final ErrorInfo BADEVENTTYPE
Invalid event type specified for this device.
Although the device supports EnableEvent, it does not support one or more of the event types specified.

ALREADYENABLED

public static final ErrorInfo ALREADYENABLED
An event handler is already enabled for this event type.
There is already an event handler bound to one or more of the events specified. To attach the new handler to the event type, first disable and disconnect the current handler using EnableEvent.

BADEVENTSIZE

public static final ErrorInfo BADEVENTSIZE
Invalid event count specified.
The ON_DATA_AVAILABLE event requires an event count greater than (0).

BADBURSTIOCOUNT

public static final ErrorInfo BADBURSTIOCOUNT
Count cannot be greater than the FIFO size for BURSTIO mode. Count must be an integer multiple of the number of channels in the scan.
When using BURSTIO, the count cannot be larger than the FIFO size.
